Supercopa Libertadores 1988

First stage
[Feb 10 and 25]
Independiente (ARG) - Cruzeiro (BRA)                    1-2  0-1
  [Merlini; Vilmar, Hamilton]
  [Heriberto]
[Feb 24 and Mar 3]
Racing Club (ARG) - Santos (BRA)                        2-0  0-0
  [Iglesias, Colombatti]
[Mar 2 and 16]
Boca Juniors (ARG) - Grêmio (BRA)                       1-0  0-2
  [Comas]
  [Lima, Cuca]
[Mar 30 and Apr 5]
Estudiantes (ARG) - Flamengo (BRA)                      1-1  0-3
  [Gissi; Bebeto]
  [Luiz Henrique, Bebeto(2)]
[Apr 6 and 15]
Peñarol (URU) - Argentinos Juniors (ARG)                1-0  0-2
  [Herrera]
  [Espíndola, Batista]
[Apr 13 and 20]
Olimpia (PAR) - River Plate (ARG)                       2-0  0-4
  [Ramírez, Mendoza]
  [Alzamendi(2), J.Da Silva(2)]
Nacional (URU) bye

Quarterfinals
[Apr 28 and May 4]
Nacional (URU) - Flamengo (BRA)                         3-0  2-0
  [Lemos, Olivera(2)]
  [W.Castro(2)]
[May 3 and 11]
Grêmio (BRA) - River Plate (ARG)                        1-0  1-3
  [Valdo]
  [Alfinete o/g, Alzamendi(2); Lima]
[May 5 and 18]
Cruzeiro (BRA) - Argentinos Juniors (ARG)               1-0  1-0
  [Ramón]
  [Heriberto]
Racing Club (ARG) bye

Semifinals
[May 25 and Jun 1]
Racing Club (ARG) - River Plate (ARG)                   2-1  1-1
  [W.Fernández(2); Borelli]
  [N.Gutiérrez; N.Fabbri]
[May 30 and Jun 3]
Nacional (URU) - Cruzeiro (BRA)                         3-2  0-1  [away goals]
  [Olivera(2), Vargas; Careca, Adhemir]
  [Robson]

Final  [Jun 13 and 18]
Racing Club (ARG) - Cruzeiro (BRA)                      2-1  1-1
  [W.Fernández, Colombatti; Robson]
  [Robson; Catalán]

Topscorers: Sergio Oliveira (Nacional) and Antonio Alzamendi (River) 4

